Public Domain

The I Ching (Book of Changes) is an ancient Chinese text dating to
approximately 1000 BCE. The James Legge English translation was
published in 1882 and is in the public domain.

Translator: James Legge (1882)
Source: https://www.sacred-texts.com/ich/index.htm

The hexagram interpretations in this deck are original summaries
inspired by traditional meanings, not reproductions of any specific
copyrighted translation.
